        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 5:48PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Collierville, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Piperton, Lenow, Fisherville, Collierville, Kirk, Elba, Canadaville,
Cordova, Rossville, Germantown, Olive Branch, and Memphis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
